T* (before a regulatory cutoff in six weeks. I was tech lead for a team of four. The stakes were a potential processing halt) Tj
T* (if we missed the date. I mapped every field mapping and exception path in week one, split work into schema) Tj
T* (validation versus production cutover, and ran daily fifteen-minute standups focused only on blockers. I took the) Tj
T* (riskiest piece — the idempotent replay logic — myself. On day twelve we found the bank's sandbox dropped) Tj
T* (duplicate trace numbers; I escalated to their integration team and got a documented workaround. We went live on) Tj
T* (day thirty-eight, two days early, and the first production week had zero settlement exceptions tied to the migration.) Tj
