(Response: At LedgerPay almost everything I ship is Go. Typical layout: cmd/ for binaries, internal/ for domain) Tj
T* (packages, thin HTTP handlers that delegate to a service layer. I use context for cancellation everywhere, structured) Tj
T* (logging with trace IDs propagated from our ingress, and table-driven tests on pure logic. Concurrency-wise I prefer) Tj
T* (errgroup for bounded parallel work — like parsing bank file rows in workers with a fixed pool — rather than) Tj
T* (unbounded goroutines. I've also learned to be disciplined about not leaking goroutines on retries; we had an incident) Tj
T* (once from a forgotten timer channel that taught the team to always tie worker lifetimes to context cancel. I'm not a) Tj
T* (generics power user, but interfaces for storage boundaries — file store, ledger client — make testing with fakes) Tj
T* (straightforward.) Tj
